Olanrewaju James, popularly called Baba Ijesha, detained by the police for alleged sexual assault, has been granted bail. His lawyer, Adesina Ogunlana, confirmed this yesterday. “He was granted bail about one hour ago. We are working to perfect the bail. He was granted bail on health grounds. He has not been released. He will be released after his bail conditions have been perfected,” he said. Among the bail conditions listed by the lawyer for Baba Ijesha’s release are two reliable sureties – one of them must be a level 10 officer, a blood relation and N500,000 bail bond in like sum.